=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
talked</a>, over the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/35947004.223415/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVz=
LzIwMjItMDItMTUveW91LWdldC10aGUtY3J5cHRvLXJ1bGVzLXlvdS1wYXktZm9yP2NtcGlkPUJ=
CRDA3MDMyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dG=
VyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDcwMyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cB43b16292" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_=
blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;">years</a>, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/35947004.223415/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlua=
W9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDEtMjcveW91LWdldC10aGUtY3J5cHRvLXJ1bGVzLXlvdS13YW50=
P2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MDMyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1=
uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDcwMyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cB0150b9af" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;">about</a> how the crypto industry frequ=
ently says that it wants the SEC (or the Commodity Futures Trading Commissi=
on, or Congress) to write rules regulating cryptocurrency markets, so that =
the industry can have regulatory clarity and get on with building the futur=
e of finance or whatever. Instead, crypto people complain, there is =E2=80=
=9Cregulation by enforcement=E2=80=9D: Rather than writing clear rules sayi=
ng what is allowed, the SEC just decides on a case-by-case basis what=C2=A0=
<em>isn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>allowed, and then sues people who already did i=
t to make them pay big fines.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now, I sometimes think that these complaints a=
re overstated =E2=80=94=C2=A0I think that a lot of crypto projects=C2=A0<a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35947004.223415/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDgtMDMvdGVycmEt=
aXMtdXN1YWxseS1hLXNlY3VyaXR5P2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MDMyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWR=
pdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDcwMyZ1dG1fY2FtcG=
FpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb810e2ba" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"><em>obvious=
ly=C2=A0</em>violate longstanding securities laws</a>, and it=E2=80=99s jus=
t wishful thinking to complain about a lack of clarity =E2=80=94=C2=A0but I=
 am <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35947004.22341=
5/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMTMvY=
3J5cHRvLXdhbnRzLXNvbWUtc2VjLXJ1bGVzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MDMyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0=
bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDcwMyZ1dG1=
fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCaa991175" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">broa=
dly sympathetic</a> to them. It would probably be better to have clear rule=
s than to have to interpolate the rules from backward-looking enforcement a=
ctions.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the way that the SEC actually makes rules =
is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It writes some rules.</li>=09<li styl=
e=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It proposes them publicly.</li>=09<li style=3D"ma=
rgin-bottom: 5px;">There=E2=80=99s a period for industry participants and i=
nterested bystanders to submit comments about the rules.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The SEC considers the comments and puts out final =
rules.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Anyone who doesn=E2=80=99t =
like the rules can sue.=C2=A0 The SEC=E2=80=99s authority to regulate crypt=
o (or anything) is contested, and even if it has the authority to regulate,=
 it has to follow proper procedures and not act arbitrarily. Whatever the r=
ules are, you can find arguments against them.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-b=
ottom: 5px;">In 2024, the person who sues=C2=A0<em>will obviously win</em>.=
 The US Supreme Court is suspicious of rulemaking by regulatory agencies, b=
ut <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35947004.223415=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMTkvaX=
MtdGhlLXNlYy11bmNvbnN0aXR1dGlvbmFsP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MDMyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0b=
V9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDcwMyZ1dG1f=
Y2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf019c2e9" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">some =
of the lower courts</a> are=C2=A0<em>way more suspicious</em>, and everybod=
y knows this and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3=
5947004.223415/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQt=
MDYtMTYvaGVkZ2UtZnVuZHMtYXJlLWZpZ2h0aW5nLXRoZS1zZWMtZnJvbS1mb3J0LXdvcnRoLXR=
leGFzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MDMyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdX=
JjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDcwMyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5b713860" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">can bring their lawsuit in a court=
</a> that will definitely strike down the rules.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin=
-bottom: 5px;">And then there is some long appeal process, at the end of wh=
ich there=E2=80=99s a decent chance that the=C2=A0rules will be struck down=
, and the SEC has to go back to the beginning and propose new rules.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Even this is oversimplified: Actually =
different people can sue at different times in different courts over differ=
ent aspects of the rules, leading to even more confusion about what the rul=
es are.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The incentives, for the SEC, are bad. If it ma=
kes new rules, that is a lot of work, and those rules will be attacked from=
 every angle. Probably they will be struck down, in ways that limit the SEC=
=E2=80=99s power and create=C2=A0<em>greater=C2=A0</em>confusion about what=
 is allowed.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile if the SEC just sees some crypto pro=
ject that it doesn=E2=80=99t like, it can sue that project =E2=80=94=C2=A0p=
robably in a court of=C2=A0<em>its=C2=A0</em>choosing =E2=80=94 say =E2=80=
=9Cthis violates longstanding securities law,=E2=80=9D and have a decent ch=
ance (<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35947004.223=
415/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDctMTQ=
vcmlwcGxlLWlzLWEtc2VjdXJpdHktYW5kLWl0LWlzbi10P2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MDMyNF9NT05FWV=
NUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0M=
DcwMyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf75834be" it=
emprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;">not a certainty!</a>) of winning. Its chances are better not only bec=
ause it can pick a more sympathetic court, but also because it can pick a <=
em>less=C2=A0</em>sympathetic antagonist: It can argue =E2=80=9Cwe need the=
 power to regulate crypto=E2=80=9D in a case where <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35947004.223415/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZX=
