uled.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The lawsuit now goes back to the district cour=
t to be heard by another judge. The appeals court said it didn=E2=80=99t lo=
ok at the merits of the case.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/35947004.223415/aHR0cHM6Ly93dzMuY2EyLnVzY291cnRzLmdv=
di9kZWNpc2lvbnMvaXN5c3F1ZXJ5L2Q5ZDNiZTg2LTRmMjktNDhiNS1hYTBlLTQxOTc0OTAzMTc=
yZi8yL2RvYy8yMS0yOTA1X29wbi5wZGYjeG1sPWh0dHBzOi8vd3czLmNhMi51c2NvdXJ0cy5nb3=
YvZGVjaXNpb25zL2lzeXNxdWVyeS9kOWQzYmU4Ni00ZjI5LTQ4YjUtYWEwZS00MTk3NDkwMzE3M=
mYvMi9oaWxpdGUv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8b547822" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">appellate decisi=
on</a>. The lawsuit is an antitrust case, alleging that the 10 banks =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0basically all the big names =E2=80=94=C2=A0conspired to restrict e=
lectronic trading of corporate bonds so they could make more money on odd-l=
ot trades. Judge Liman <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/35947004.223415/aHR0cHM6Ly9sYXcuanVzdGlhLmNvbS9jYXNlcy9mZWRlcmFsL2Rpc3=
RyaWN0LWNvdXJ0cy9uZXcteW9yay9ueXNkY2UvMToyMDIwY3YwMzE1NC81MzYwMjMvMTQ3Lw/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa963a520" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">dismissed it in 2021</a>. Now it i=
s back because, apparently unknown to him, his wife owned =E2=80=9Cas much =
as $15,000 in Bank of America stock,=E2=80=9D though she sold it months bef=
ore his decision on the case.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know Lewis Liman=E2=80=99s net=
 worth, but he was <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/35947004.223415/aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvTGV3aXNfSi5fTGltYW=
4/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa871d95e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"it=
emscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">a partner at big New York law =
firms</a> for 20 years, so I suspect that =E2=80=9Cas much as $15,000=E2=80=
=9D represents rather less than 1% of his family=E2=80=99s assets. If the L=
imans had put all of their money in S&amp;P 500 stock index funds =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0sort of the default =E2=80=9Cnot making any investment decisions=E2=
=80=9D approach =E2=80=94 then Bank of America Corp. stock would represent =
about 0.54% of their portfolio.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnot=
e-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !imp=
ortant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co., another defendant in this lawsuit, woul=
d be 1.15%. Citigroup Inc., Wells Fargo &amp; Co., Goldman Sachs Group Inc.=
 and Morgan Stanley =E2=80=94=C2=A0the other US defendants =E2=80=94=C2=A0w=
ould add another 1.25% or so.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Presumably not all of their money is in stocks=
, but still. The point is that it would be somewhat unusual for a wealthy U=
S citizen=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>to have economic exposure equivalent to ow=
ning $15,000 worth of stock in one or more of the big banks. If no judge wi=
th that much exposure can hear an antitrust case against all of the big ban=
ks, then it=E2=80=99s possible that no judge=C2=A0<em>at all=C2=A0</em>can =
hear the case.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously that=E2=80=99s not right. In fact <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35947004.223415/aHR0=
cHM6Ly93d3cubGF3LmNvcm5lbGwuZWR1L3VzY29kZS90ZXh0LzI4LzQ1NQ/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cB62fbcc44" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">the rule</a> requires a judge to recuse himself =
if he or his spouse has an =E2=80=9Cequitable interest, however small,=E2=
=80=9D in a company involved in the case, but =E2=80=9Cownership in a mutua=
l or common investment fund that holds securities is not a =E2=80=98financi=
al interest=E2=80=99 in such securities unless the judge participates in th=
e management of the fund.=E2=80=9D So owning an index fund that <em>obvious=
ly=C2=A0</em>owns stock in all the big banks does not count as a financial =
interest, but direct ownership of stock by your spouse, =E2=80=9Chowever sm=
all,=E2=80=9D even if you don=E2=80=99t know about it, does.=C2=A0</p>
