<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When we last discussed Canna Global, I pointed=
 out that it is not that uncommon for a company to (1) need money, (2) find=
 potential investors who are willing to give the company money in exchange =
for stock, but (3) not have enough stock to give them. That was roughly Can=
na Global=E2=80=99s situation, but it comes up more often when a company=E2=
=80=99s charter says =E2=80=9Cthis company can issue up to 100 million shar=
es,=E2=80=9D or whatever, and the company has issued 99 million and wants t=
o issue more.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The simplest solution, in that case, is to ask=
 shareholders to vote to amend the charter to authorize more shares. But th=
at takes time, and sometimes you need the money now. In that case, the less=
 simple solution is to issue some sort of IOU for stock: =E2=80=9CYou give =
us the money now, and in exchange we=E2=80=99ll promise to give you the sto=
ck when we can get shareholders to authorize it.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Usually this IOU takes the form of =E2=80=9Cbl=
ank check preferred stock=E2=80=9D: The investors get a new special preferr=
ed stock (not covered by the charter=E2=80=99s limitation on shares), and t=
he preferred converts into common stock whenever the company gets around to=
 amending its charter to authorize more stock.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">All of this can be a bit more urgent for=C2=A0=
<em>banks</em>. A bank is a highly leveraged pile of assets, which means:</=
p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Its stock can go down a lot. You migh=
t think =E2=80=9Cwe have 56 million shares outstanding and=C2=A0100 million=
 authorized shares, so we can sell 44 million more, which=C2=A0is plenty; t=
he stock trades at like $25 per share, so that=E2=80=99s like a billion dol=
lars of financing room.=E2=80=9D And then the stock goes to $5 and it=E2=80=
=99s not enough.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If it needs money=
, it needs money=C2=A0<em>right now</em>. If a bank announces =E2=80=9Cwe=
=E2=80=99re going to raise money as soon as we get this shareholder vote,=
=E2=80=9D it is not going to last until the shareholder vote.</li>
</ol>
